1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:02,120
Uncle Durmuş sold his house.

2
00:00:02,440 --> 00:00:03,960
Find out who bought it for me.

3
00:00:04,480 --> 00:00:06,960
I can find out but… why?

4
00:00:09,520 --> 00:00:12,600
Maybe we can buy this house for Mercan.

5
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:14,640
She loves this place.

6
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:18,840
That village house they went to,
it seems to have been sold recently.

7
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:21,280
Find out who bought it for me.

8
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:23,721
In fact, the moment you find
out, offer double to buy it.

9
00:00:24,920 --> 00:00:26,520
You two will plant this one.

10
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:28,920
Since you say you love this place so much,

11
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,720
As it grows, as it gets stronger,

12
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,800
wherever you are,

13
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:36,200
your love will grow stronger too.

14
00:00:36,680 --> 00:00:38,840
Look, if you give even a drop of love

15
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:42,240
Ateş, the man won't budge.

16
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:45,160
He seems likely to accept Nezir's offer.

17
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:48,080
Nezir has opened his purse
strings out of jealousy.

18
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:49,960
Crazy guy.

19
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:53,320
Send me the info for that
man. Let me talk to him.

20
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,760
The person you're waiting for isn't coming.

21
00:00:56,200 --> 00:01:00,320
He can't sell a house he
already sold, after all…

22
00:01:01,880 --> 00:01:02,960
What are you talking about!

23
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:05,440
I bought the house, Nezir.

24
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:08,320
I'm leaving, Cemal.

25
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:11,840
Because no one loves me. No one wants me.

26
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,160
Goodbye.

27
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:14,960
One day I will come back.

28
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:17,280
I'll be everyone's nightmare.

29
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:22,480
I will make you pay for
everything you've done to me.

30
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Ateş Karahan!

31
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,680
Mercan.

32
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:35,640
You kidnapped my bride-to-be once.

33
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:36,760
Look...

34
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:38,360
Now I'm doing the kidnapping.

35
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:42,600
No. Mercan!

36
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:48,800
You've been on this journey with
Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

37
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:52,120
Every twist, every
heartbreak. Every moment.

38
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,959
And now we reach the end.

39
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:56,879
This isn't something to watch alone.

40
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:59,199
This is something we experience together.

41
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:04,760
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not
be available on any memberships.

42
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:08,320
They will premiere on YouTube
for all of us at the same time.

43
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:09,839
One moment.

44
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:12,719
One story. One ending.

45
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:15,279
So grab your comfy
blanket and a huge bucket

46
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:18,280
of popcorn for one final twist.

47
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,360
Let's be there together.

48
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,360
Mercan?

49
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,080
Mercan?

50
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Are you okay?

51
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:27,600
Ateş!

52
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:33,840
Mercan. Don't be scared.

53
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:37,600
You don't need to be
scared when I'm with you.

54
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,520
Ateş...

55
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:44,560
My love, I had a very bad nightmare.

56
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,280
You've come to, thank God.

57
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:50,160
Now all your nightmares will end.

58
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,560
We'll be together forever.

59
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,880
Nezih! What have you done?

60
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,400
Untie me!

61
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,600
I can't, Marjan.

62
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:51,560
I'm sorry.

63
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,840
Stop talking nonsense.

64
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,800
Untie my hands, quickly!

65
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:11,600
Enough! I want to leave here!

66
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,800
Marjan.

67
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,120
From now on, we're together.

68
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:23,920
You'd better get used to it.

69
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,120
You can't keep me here by force!

70
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,120
Keep still.

71
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:36,680
Don't make me tie your feet.

72
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:42,880
I will teach you to love me.

73
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,400
Then you won't want to leave anyway.

74
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,080
So don't force me.

75
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,920
I've arranged everything for us.

76
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,800
Are you crazy?

77
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:02,880
Can love be forced?

78
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:07,120
By kidnapping and imprisoning...

79
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:12,800
I'm perfectly sane.

80
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,040
You forced me to do this.

81
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:28,960
But it's okay.

82
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,000
We'll escape from here on a boat.

83
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,560
Just the two of us.

84
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:39,440
Look.

85
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,800
Our passports are even ready.

86
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,480
We're leaving tomorrow.

87
00:06:57,720 --> 00:07:00,280
Nezir, stop deluding yourself.

88
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,200
This... This is...

89
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,880
What you're doing is so
absurd, so meaningless.

90
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,960
I will never love you.

91
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,680
Because Ateş is the only one I love.

92
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:21,120
And that will never change.

93
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,040
Let's see...

94
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,360
We've only just begun...

95
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,839
I will teach you to love me, Mercan.

96
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:33,400
You will love me a lot.

97
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,360
A whole lot.

98
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,120
Oh, God.

99
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,800
He took Mercan away.

100
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,920
He kidnapped her right in front of my eyes!

101
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,680
Cemal.

102
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,200
I can't take it anymore, Cemal.

103
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:22,040
I know, brother.

104
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,200
I know, don't worry.

105
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,560
But you have to endure.

106
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:27,440
You have to endure so we can
find Mercan safe and sound.

107
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:32,400
What do you think
Mercan is doing right now?

108
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:36,200
My God, give me strength.

109
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:38,760
He won't hurt her, will he?

110
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,600
He wouldn't have done anything to Mercan.

111
00:08:40,680 --> 00:08:42,856
Ates, what are you talking
about? He can't do anything.

112
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,760
He can't touch a hair
on her head, don't worry.

113
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,416
I'm going to tear him to pieces.

114
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,160
Once I get my hands on him,

115
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,480
I'm going to kill him.

116
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,640
Alright, Ates, just
calm down. That's enough.

117
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,720
Look, you need to stay calm.

118
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,240
I can't stay calm.

119
00:08:58,840 --> 00:08:59,840
You will if you have to.

120
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,600
You have no other choice.

121
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,280
It's all my fault.

122
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,720
I shouldn't have left her.

123
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:10,240
I shouldn't have left her
alone for even a second.

124
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,920
It's all my fault, mine!

125
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:18,840
Alright, Ates, blaming
yourself right now won't help us.

126
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:20,576
That man has written
the book on wickedness.

127
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,400
It's not your fault.

128
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,960
Whatever he writes.

129
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,840
Are all our money and men for nothing?

130
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:28,720
Something like this
should never have happened.

131
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:31,000
Yes, it shouldn't have
happened. You're right.

132
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:34,440
We've informed the police.
Our men are searching too.

133
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,320
The police and us, from all sides.

134
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,160
We're searching everywhere meticulously.

135
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,840
Check all escape routes, Cemal.

136
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,720
This man kidnapped her by boat before.

137
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,600
Alright, I'll handle it.

138
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,160
Tell me, Vedat.

139
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:51,160
We found

140
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,320
Nezir's car abandoned, Mr. Cemal.

141
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:56,960
Alright, send me the location.
We're heading out immediately.

142
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,400
Let's go, come on, let's go!

143
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,320
What do you want?

144
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:18,200
Look, if you think about it for a bit,
you'll understand this isn't the way.

145
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,280
Come to your senses already.

146
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,520
Untie me.

147
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:24,400
Talking didn't work.

148
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,880
I begged, it didn't work.

149
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,000
I was kind, it didn't work.

150
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:36,560
So, this is how it's going to be.

151
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,600
I have no other choice.

152
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:57,320
My father always said, the weak get what's
due to them, but the strong seize that share.

153
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:05,680
If it can't be done nicely,
then by force, Mercan.

154
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,840
I will teach you to love
me, even if it's by force.

155
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,120
Serhat, this won't work.

156
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,760
You're hurting yourself and me.

157
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:26,280
Do you want to go to jail for
something that won't happen?

158
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:31,960
We were friends, you and I.

159
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,480
Nothing more ever happened between us.

160
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:38,360
And it never will.

161
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:42,080
Don't turn this into an
obsession and ruin your life.

162
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:45,160
This isn't an obsession, Mercan.

163
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,040
This is love.

164
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,880
We were getting married, weren't we?

165
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,080
Isn't that right?

166
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,360
Nezir.

167
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:03,400
If that guy hadn't shown
up, you'd be my wife.

168
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,400
Nezir, stop talking nonsense!

169
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:10,440
I was never going to be your wife!

170
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,000
I'm not the one talking nonsense, you are.

171
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:18,080
You were the one talking nonsense
when you rejected me and chose that guy.

172
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,320
But I understand you.

173
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,080
I'm not angry.

174
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,280
Your family confused you.

175
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:34,560
You got caught up in wrong
ideas, but don't worry.

176
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:36,440
I'll fix everything.

177
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,720
Hold on tight!

178
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,200
I'll fix everything...

179
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:43,840
I said don't touch me!

180
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:44,800
What are you doing?

181
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,000
Take your hands off.

182
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:47,040
I said don't touch me!

183
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:48,560
Don't you dare touch me, let go!

184
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,800
Let go! I'll ruin you! Don't touch me!

185
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,880
You'll understand. Mercan will understand.

186
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:55,720
You'll understand what's right.

187
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:58,000
That man isn't your destiny.

188
00:12:58,040 --> 00:12:59,040
Let go!
It's me.

189
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:02,880
Let go! You're disgusting!

190
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:04,120
It was always me. Mine.

191
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,400
Don't touch me! Stay away from me!

192
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:20,920
Snap out of it!

193
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,080
Ah!
Get off!

194
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:32,880
Is she gone?
Alright, boss.

195
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,640
And you're holding a gun like that!

196
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,240
PUT IT DOWN!

197
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:37,520
Put it down!

198
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,600
Have him sit here.

199
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,280
Son.

200
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,120
Connect it to his screen!

201
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,320
In my mouth.

202
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,880
Let go!

203
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:12,680
Ateş, his car is here.

204
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,200
What's the situation?

205
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:21,000
We're scanning the entire area with drones,
but there's no trace of her, unfortunately.

206
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:24,520
Ateş Karasu!

207
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:27,000
You kidnapped my daughter-in-law.

208
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:29,720
Look, now I'm kidnapping yours.

209
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:33,920
Nezir!

210
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,920
I'm going to kill you!

211
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:15,160
My dear, my beautiful.

212
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:38,880
Where is Mercan?

213
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:40,480
What did you do to her?

214
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,360
We played a little game.

215
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:47,960
When there's a bit of pushing and
shoving up close, things like this happen.

216
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,520
It's very normal.
Mercan said goodbye.

217
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,080
I won't let you live.

218
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,816
I'm going to break those hands of yours.

219
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:59,520
Those hands that dared to touch
her, I'm going to shatter them!

220
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,000
You can't do anything.

221
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,240
Show me Mercan!

222
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,680
Hold on, my beautiful-eyed love.

223
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:15,720
Hold on.

224
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,120
Ateş! Ateş!

225
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:20,720
Don't be scared!

226
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:21,840
Never!
I will find you.

227
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:23,680
Alright.

228
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:30,800
You were telling me you were sad.

229
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:43,440
Didn't I tell you I'd make you
pay the price if you messed with me?

230
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:47,080
I always kept my word.

231
00:16:49,040 --> 00:16:50,360
And now I've taken Mercan back.

232
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:51,440
Don't touch her!

233
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:57,240
NEVER!

234
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,680
Don't you dare touch her!

235
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:01,280
I'm going to tear you to pieces!

236
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:02,640
I'm going to kill you!

237
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:05,680
You're not in a position to give me orders.

238
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,480
I won.

239
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:18,120
And this is the last
time you'll see Mercan.

240
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:20,960
Consider it a consolation gift.

241
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,520
She was mine and she'll always be mine.

242
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,240
Mercan, don't you dare be scared.

243
00:17:26,360 --> 00:17:27,440
Don't be scared, my beauty.

244
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:34,000
You know me, trust me.

245
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:40,800
Even if you go to the other side of
the world, as long as you're breathing,

246
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:43,360
I'll be right behind you!

247
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:45,160
Don't bother us anymore.

248
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:47,400
Even if you wanted to, you couldn't.

249
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,040
Because you won't find us.

250
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:56,560
I'll pull you out of
every hole you crawl into!

251
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:57,760
Look at that guy!

252
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,920
As long as you live, you'll have no peace!

253
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,560
Where's that courage in you?

254
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:06,200
You're a coward! If you're a man,

255
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:11,360
Well then...

256
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,520
First, we'll get rid of you.

257
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,040
Sir.

258
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:31,360
Where is this man? Where?

259
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:36,760
Hold on, Mercan, hold
on, my beautiful, hold on.

260
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:39,400
Find that man!

261
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:43,000
Alright, alright, pass
it to the news center.

262
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:45,360
Send all the reinforcements you can.

263
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,360
Alright, hurry up.

264
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:51,920
I talked to our guys.

265
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:54,776
I asked for reinforcements.
They'll send as many as they can.

266
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,880
We'll hit all of Nezir's
places from all four sides.

267
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:07,560
Demet might know.

268
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:08,680
Come on, let's go.

269
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:35,240
I didn't do that, Dorak.

270
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:38,440
On the contrary, nothing
would have happened to you.

271
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:40,360
Please, go.

272
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:43,920
You broke me.

273
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:45,680
And if I speak, I will break you.

274
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:52,880
Okay. Look.

275
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:58,360
I wasn't going to lie.

276
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:00,960
Forgive me.

277
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:05,080
I'll forgive you on one condition.

278
00:20:06,040 --> 00:20:08,320
You will apologize to Çiçek and her family.

279
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:14,280
If you say you can't,
then you'll forget me.

280
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:16,960
What about me?

281
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:18,200
I've said what I had to say.

282
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:20,800
That’s all

283
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:23,480
Raise them, bring them up.

284
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:26,280
Then forget them, is that it?

285
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:32,640
Are you going to erase
your mother for them?

286
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:08,360
Nezir, look, turn away from this path.

287
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:11,080
I don't know how else to explain it to you.

288
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,240
I don't love you.

289
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:15,160
And I never will.

290
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,160
I love Ateş.

291
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:20,760
Look, one day you'll love someone.

292
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:22,200
And they'll love you back.

293
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:27,720
You never loved me.

294
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:32,240
Why did you never see me?

295
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:41,520
That's why I...

296
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,040
Nazir, look.

297
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,800
This isn't how it works, don't do this.

298
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:48,200
You're hurting yourself and me.

299
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:53,920
I really wonder what
that man has that I don't.

300
00:21:58,320 --> 00:22:00,240
He came to torment you.

301
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:04,080
I...

302
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:07,000
I just wanted to make you happy.

303
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:15,960
Remember?

304
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:17,920
Sometimes when you left school,

305
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:19,680
you and Demet would come to our place.

306
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:23,520
I would be so happy to see you at home.

307
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:28,120
My hands and feet would get all
tangled up, I wouldn't know what to do.

308
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,560
We were so small then.

309
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:40,640
Back then, I used to dream.

310
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:42,640
That one day I would marry you.

311
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:48,520
It was so close.

312
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,720
It was so close.

313
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:56,560
If that guy named Ateş hadn't
come, we would be married right now.

314
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:03,920
I had one chance.

315
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,960
If you had come with me, we
would have been very happy.

316
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:11,000
But what did you do?

317
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,840
You chose your enemy.

318
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:21,920
You chose the man who came to destroy your family,
not the man who would lay the world at your feet.

319
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:26,640
Why didn't you give me a chance?

320
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:30,720
Because I'm in love with Ateş.

321
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,160
You're not.

322
00:23:32,360 --> 00:23:33,680
You're not, you're not.

323
00:23:45,080 --> 00:23:46,360
You think you are...

324
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,360
Look, I'm the right man for you.

325
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,800
You'll understand that when you're mine.

326
00:23:55,520 --> 00:23:56,520
I'd die.

327
00:23:56,840 --> 00:23:59,000
If necessary, I'd kill, but
I still wouldn't be yours.

328
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,800
Even if you kidnap me...

329
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:02,000
Even if you lock me up!

330
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:06,120
Even if you take me to the other side of the world
and tie me up until I die, this fact won't change.

331
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:07,600
It will change, Mercan!

332
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:10,120
You've gone blind.

333
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,560
Ateş and the one who died
with him have blinded you.

334
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,560
But I will open those
beautiful eyes of yours.

335
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:23,480
Don't you dare touch me.

336
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:25,600
Your story is over, Mercan.

337
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:28,440
Ours is just beginning.

338
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:31,000
No matter what you say.

339
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:33,320
I love Ateş.

340
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:38,160
Neither you, nor anyone else...

341
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:40,440
No one can separate us, understood?

342
00:24:41,040 --> 00:24:42,040
Shut up!

343
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:43,640
Shut up!

344
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:45,680
Shut up!

345
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,480
Shut up!

346
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:49,880
Shut up!

347
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:53,240
Ah!

348
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:03,560
Since this won't change
as long as the fire exists,

349
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:12,040
then I'll extinguish that fire.

350
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:28,160
You asked for this.

351
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,920
If you harm a single hair on her head,

352
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:34,520
I won't let you live, understand?

353
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:36,280
I'll destroy you.

354
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:37,760
If...

355
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:40,240
If you're going to kill
someone, kill me, leave her alone.

356
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,120
Kill you?

357
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:53,160
If you don't want her to get
hurt, you'll do exactly as I say.

358
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,760
Otherwise, I'll go and kill her.

359
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:29,040
If anything happens to her
because of me, I can't live.

360
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:31,080
I can't live.

361
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,360
Atıf abi, what happened?

362
00:26:51,320 --> 00:26:52,320
Where is Nezir?

363
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:54,080
I don't know.

364
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:55,800
What is this now, what's going on?

365
00:26:55,840 --> 00:26:57,216
Where is that scoundrel brother of yours?

366
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:58,440
I told you I don't know!

367
00:26:59,520 --> 00:27:01,160
You're his brother, you must know.

368
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:07,440
You're going to tell me where he went.

369
00:27:08,280 --> 00:27:09,560
You know your brother after all.

370
00:27:10,440 --> 00:27:11,520
Calm down.

371
00:27:12,280 --> 00:27:13,280
What are these manners?

372
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:16,800
And why would I lie to you? If
I say I don't know, I don't know.

373
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:17,520
Easy, alright.

374
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:18,960
She doesn't know also, apparently.

375
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:20,080
You'll think!

376
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:23,520
You'll tell me every hole he
could be hiding in. Do you hear me?

377
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:24,440
Huh?

378
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:28,800
I'm going to find him. Whoever
greeted him, whoever helped him,

379
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:31,280
I'll punish everyone.

380
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:34,816
Okay, you calm down,
come here for a second.

381
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:35,840
Come on.

382
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:40,640
Are you going to tell me what happened?

383
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:42,520
Nezir kidnapped Mercan.

384
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:44,440
What?

385
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:05,440
I didn't know, I had no idea.

386
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:09,040
Mr. Ateş.

387
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:11,120
Is there anything we can do?

388
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:12,536
If there is, tell us right away.

389
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:14,960
If necessary, we'll go door
to door and search for them all.

390
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:19,800
Exactly, we'll do whatever
it takes. We're with you.

391
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:21,160
Exactly, bro.

392
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:23,880
Thank you.

393
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:32,040
Just in case, if anything comes to mind
about where she might go, let me know.

394
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:43,360
I'm coming too.

395
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,960
She won't harm Ms. Mercan, will she?

396
00:28:49,840 --> 00:28:50,600
I hope not.

397
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:52,000
No, no, she won't.

398
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:53,640
She won't.

399
00:28:55,880 --> 00:29:00,440
Yes, what she did was bad, but she did
it because she wanted you by her side.

400
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:02,440
And what was the result?

401
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,720
She lost me completely.

402
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:12,040
Would a person lie to
their own child, Çiçek?

403
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:20,400
When she should have been happy with my happiness,
standing by my side, behind me, what did she do?

404
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:23,560
She tried to separate me
from you with lies and deceit.

405
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:25,840
This isn't family.

406
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,400
What have I ever seen from the family

407
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:38,680
Have we ever sat at a table
and had a meal together even once?

408
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:43,360
Did she ever hug me even once?

409
00:29:43,960 --> 00:29:46,640
Even once, did I feel them by my side?

410
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:47,960
No.

411
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:49,320
No to all of it.

412
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:53,760
I didn't know what family meant, Çiçek.

413
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:55,760
Here...

414
00:29:56,760 --> 00:29:58,200
I learned with you.

415
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:00,600
And I loved it so much, Çiçek.

416
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:06,960
Family is everything in the world.

417
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:12,240
I don't want to feel that
loneliness again, Çiçek.

418
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:25,480
I'm always by your side.

419
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:29,440
We are your family.

420
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:31,480
We are all by your side.

421
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:35,120
What does being alone even mean?

422
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:36,680
Don't you dare say that again.

423
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:37,960
Okay?

424
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:49,720
I love you.

425
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:16,560
Did you find my daughter?

426
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:19,160
Tell me, is there any news from Mercan?

427
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:26,200
Not yet. We're looking.

428
00:31:30,320 --> 00:31:31,320
Where could she be?

429
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:33,960
Who knows what state my daughter is in.

430
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:39,080
Ms. Nermin, we'll find her, don't worry.

431
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:42,200
Mercan is a strong girl. She
won't let Nezire get away with this.

432
00:31:43,600 --> 00:31:45,520
What happened, Cemal?
Hasn't she been found yet?

433
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:46,600
No, Ms. Müzeyyen.

434
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:48,080
We still haven't found her.

435
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:50,040
It's like the earth
opened up and swallowed her.

436
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:54,160
Oh, for goodness sake!

437
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:55,680
I hope she's found.

438
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:56,840
I hope so.

439
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,480
Cemal, come on, let's go.

440
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:09,080
You're enjoying this, aren't you?

441
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:12,136
I'm suffering here
because my daughter is gone.

442
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,120
And you're celebrating inside.

443
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:18,400
You two-faced fraud.

444
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:21,360
And then asking where she is and all.

445
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:23,320
It's all lies.

446
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:25,280
You're a liar!

447
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:28,360
But my daughter will come back here.

448
00:32:29,040 --> 00:32:31,000
Then I'll see about you.

449
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:40,960
Is there anything I can do,
Ateş brother? Whatever it takes.

450
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:45,000
It would be good if you could
reach one of Mezen's companies.

451
00:32:45,040 --> 00:32:47,480
Maybe someone saw or heard something.

452
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:49,560
Okay, abi, I'll check.

453
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:51,120
I'll reach out to whoever I can.

454
00:33:02,800 --> 00:33:04,200
Where is he?

455
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:08,160
He'll be here soon.

456
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:13,040
Brother...

457
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:15,160
It's very difficult, I understand you.

458
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:16,800
But we will find Mercan.

459
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:19,800
Don't have any doubt about that.

460
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:22,440
Besides, you're not a
man to give in to despair.

461
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:23,600
Don't be like this.

462
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,280
What if something happens to her?

463
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:33,600
What if I lose her too, like Eylul?

464
00:33:41,600 --> 00:33:42,600
I can't bear that.

465
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:49,240
The fear of losing Meryem is too heavy.

466
00:33:53,120 --> 00:33:55,520
I've overcome every mountain,
climbed out of every well, but

467
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:57,160
I'll drown in this.

468
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:04,480
If I fall this time...

469
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:08,720
No one can get me back on my feet again.

470
00:34:21,240 --> 00:34:23,200
She doesn't show it, but
she must be very scared.

471
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:30,680
She hasn't eaten, hasn't drunk water.

472
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:35,440
No one could make her do
anything she didn't want to.

473
00:34:40,120 --> 00:34:42,280
Caught in a trap in the wilderness,

474
00:34:42,720 --> 00:34:44,640
she is like wild wolves now.

475
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:54,520
Those wolves, to avoid surrendering to the
enemy, sometimes bite off their own legs.

476
00:34:58,600 --> 00:34:59,920
But they still escape.

477
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:10,360
One of my biggest fears
is Mercan harming herself.

478
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:17,240
We have to find her as soon as possible.

479
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:45,440
Come on.

480
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:46,880
Drink a glass of water.

481
00:36:17,160 --> 00:36:18,160
Come on, look.

482
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:20,320
Come on, please have a sip.

483
00:36:28,080 --> 00:36:30,040
Come on, please have a sip of soup.

484
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:35,960
Come on, please.

485
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:37,480
Don't break my heart.

486
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:04,320
What's going on, Ateş? What's
with forcing me to come here?

487
00:37:04,920 --> 00:37:05,920
Where is Nezir?

488
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:09,080
How should I know where he is?

489
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:13,320
Where did this come from now?

490
00:37:14,720 --> 00:37:16,320
You pulled off so many schemes together.

491
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:18,240
You must know.

492
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:20,480
Tell me, where did he hide Mercan?

493
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:22,440
What?

494
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:24,560
Nezir kidnapped Mercan?

495
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:26,240
Yes.

496
00:37:28,440 --> 00:37:31,320
I don't know anything, I haven't
seen him or spoken to him in a while.

497
00:37:33,680 --> 00:37:35,200
You know everything.

498
00:37:35,640 --> 00:37:37,880
You have experience with
kidnappings after all.

499
00:37:38,200 --> 00:37:39,560
Tell me, where is Mercan?

500
00:37:43,920 --> 00:37:46,920
I don't know, Ateş. I'm telling
you the truth, I don't know.

501
00:37:49,760 --> 00:37:50,760
Get out of here! Leave!

502
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:09,040
I can't stay here anymore!

503
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:12,920
We'll check everywhere
that belongs to Nezir!

504
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:16,480
If necessary, we'll turn
all of Istanbul upside down!

505
00:38:26,520 --> 00:38:27,760
Yeah, there's nothing I can do.

506
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:28,800
When did this happen?

507
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:31,360
Why didn't you tell me, Mom?

508
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:33,600
Daughter, I just found out too.

509
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:36,640
Nezir finally caught a mouse.

510
00:38:36,760 --> 00:38:37,760
Finally, I mean.

511
00:38:39,680 --> 00:38:41,200
Weren't you on their side?

512
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:46,520
I'm doing whatever I need to
do until I achieve my plans.

513
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:49,600
I wasn't going to welcome
Haydar's daughter, was I?

514
00:38:51,160 --> 00:38:53,960
My grudge won't end until
the Yıldırımlar are finished.

515
00:38:57,480 --> 00:38:58,480
Who are you calling?

516
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:00,800
Nezir.

517
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:08,960
He's not picking up.

518
00:39:10,080 --> 00:39:12,240
I need to find out his plans, Mom.

519
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:39,000
You've been on this journey with
Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

520
00:39:39,320 --> 00:39:42,320
Every twist, every
heartbreak. Every moment.

521
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:45,159
And now we reach the end.

522
00:39:45,160 --> 00:39:47,079
This isn't something to watch alone.

523
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:49,399
This is something we experience together.

524
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:54,960
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not
be available on any memberships.

525
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:58,520
They will premiere on YouTube
for all of us at the same time.

526
00:39:58,960 --> 00:40:00,039
One moment.

527
00:40:00,040 --> 00:40:02,919
One story. One ending.

528
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:05,479
So grab your comfy
blanket and a huge bucket

529
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:08,480
of popcorn for one final twist.

530
00:40:08,600 --> 00:40:10,560
Let's be there together.

531
00:40:16,240 --> 00:40:18,480
Poor Mercan has been through so much.

532
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:20,800
It's a pity for the girl, and a sin too.

533
00:40:33,160 --> 00:40:36,520
Nezir is such a bad,
such a cunning man, really.

534
00:40:36,640 --> 00:40:39,360
The girl doesn't love you,
what don't you understand?

535
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:46,320
But Mr. Ateş really got
his buttons pushed this time.

536
00:40:48,200 --> 00:40:52,680
Oh, big bros, I swear, I
think Mr. Ateş will catch him.

537
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:56,360
And when he catches him, he'll
gouge his eyes out, seriously.

538
00:40:56,440 --> 00:40:57,680
Hah, I'm writing that down.

539
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:03,800
I agree.

540
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:05,920
But this time the
punishment will be severe.

541
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:09,160
As long as Mercan comes
back safe and sound.

542
00:41:09,240 --> 00:41:11,160
After that, let whoever do whatever.

543
00:41:13,680 --> 00:41:14,760
Will she come back, though?

544
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:21,640
Still no word.

545
00:41:23,200 --> 00:41:24,200
Oh, folks.

546
00:41:25,160 --> 00:41:26,840
Don't get pessimistic so quickly.

547
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:29,200
Please, for heaven's sake.

548
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:31,680
We talked to Mr. Cemal, too.

549
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:38,440
Of course. We said, "If you need
help, if you need to search, we're here."

550
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:46,560
Exactly. We said we'd do whatever we could.

551
00:41:47,640 --> 00:41:54,800
That was good of you. On a day like this, a person looks for
support, for help, and you said you're here. That was good, kids.

552
00:41:56,360 --> 00:41:59,560
So the soup's ready.
Shall I serve the food too?

553
00:42:01,440 --> 00:42:04,520
We will eat, my girl, but what
can I say? Who has an appetite left?

554
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:14,680
Why can't I put this earring on?

555
00:43:15,520 --> 00:43:16,800
Wait, let me help you.

556
00:43:36,200 --> 00:43:37,720
I love this earring so much.

557
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:40,400
Because it shows how well you know me.

558
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:45,640
It's like I described exactly what
I'd love, and you went and got it.

559
00:43:47,560 --> 00:43:48,560
They're so beautiful.

560
00:43:50,080 --> 00:43:51,120
You had no trouble at all.

561
00:43:56,680 --> 00:44:00,960
When you love someone a lot, you
know them better than anyone else.

562
00:44:05,640 --> 00:44:08,920
Actually, what's beautiful
isn't the earring, it's you.

563
00:44:11,160 --> 00:44:12,640
Anything I bought you would suit you.

564
00:44:15,760 --> 00:44:17,920
My wife makes my whole life beautiful.

565
00:44:41,800 --> 00:44:43,160
I'll find you, Mercan.

566
00:44:45,480 --> 00:44:46,640
Just hold on a little longer.

567
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:49,560
I'll talk.

568
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:18,040
Ateş...

569
00:45:20,480 --> 00:45:21,560
Ateş...

570
00:45:41,320 --> 00:45:42,320
Come on.

571
00:45:43,880 --> 00:45:45,520
Look, you haven't eaten anything all day.

572
00:45:47,240 --> 00:45:48,280
I brought you food.

573
00:45:49,520 --> 00:45:50,520
Untie my hands!

574
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:52,320
I'll eat myself.

575
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:55,040
No need, I'll feed you.

576
00:45:55,400 --> 00:45:56,400
Come on, open your mouth.

577
00:45:57,560 --> 00:45:59,560
You can't be scared of me, can you?

578
00:46:02,280 --> 00:46:03,560
I saw what you did just now.

579
00:46:05,520 --> 00:46:06,920
And also when Ateş was kidnapped.

580
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:12,000
You too...

581
00:46:18,840 --> 00:46:20,280
You were the one who kidnapped Ateş!

582
00:46:27,200 --> 00:46:29,480
I didn't believe Ateş back then.

583
00:46:31,040 --> 00:46:32,360
And when my father accepted it...

584
00:46:33,760 --> 00:46:34,800
Me too, of course?

585
00:46:40,680 --> 00:46:43,480
If I had finished him off there,
everything would have been different.

586
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:46,160
Come on, open your mouth.

587
00:46:55,840 --> 00:46:58,120
If you're trying to get
yourself killed, I won't do it.

588
00:47:02,200 --> 00:47:03,359
Don't be stubborn, open your mouth.

589
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:04,360
I won't eat.

590
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:06,480
You can't force me to do anything.

591
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:08,320
I don't want anything from you.

592
00:47:10,520 --> 00:47:11,520
Don't be stubborn.

593
00:47:11,960 --> 00:47:12,960
Open your mouth!

594
00:47:13,280 --> 00:47:13,520
Mercan!
Let go!

595
00:47:14,040 --> 00:47:15,040
Mercan!
I said let go.

596
00:47:15,880 --> 00:47:16,880
You need to eat.
Come on.

597
00:47:18,320 --> 00:47:19,840
Open your mouth.

598
00:47:19,880 --> 00:47:20,920
Why can't I drink?
Open it!

599
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:22,776
Open, open, open, open!
Open your mouth, Mercan.

600
00:47:22,800 --> 00:47:23,800
Come on.

601
00:47:24,720 --> 00:47:26,360
Very good.

602
00:47:28,720 --> 00:47:29,720
Look!

603
00:47:31,160 --> 00:47:32,680
Every lie has an end, doesn't it?

604
00:47:43,120 --> 00:47:46,040
I won't eat a single
bite until you let me go.

605
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:52,920
I won't drink a single drop of water.

606
00:47:53,720 --> 00:47:55,440
I'll die if I have to, understand?

607
00:47:55,600 --> 00:47:57,480
Living with you is worse than death anyway.

608
00:47:59,120 --> 00:48:01,480
If you want to fight, Mercan, so be it.

609
00:48:02,160 --> 00:48:03,520
You have to love me.

610
00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:13,680
And until you love me, you will always
be by my side and alive, understood?

611
00:48:39,520 --> 00:48:40,520
Ateş!

612
00:48:41,040 --> 00:48:42,360
Take me away!

613
00:48:44,320 --> 00:48:45,680
Please, save me.

614
00:48:47,520 --> 00:48:49,600
I can't take it anymore.

615
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:02,760
Send them. Send them too.

616
00:53:02,800 --> 00:53:04,760
I want every man you have.

617
00:53:05,760 --> 00:53:06,440
Okay.

618
00:53:06,480 --> 00:53:08,000
I'm waiting for your news.

619
00:53:08,040 --> 00:53:10,640
Even if you hear the
slightest thing, call me.

620
00:53:11,400 --> 00:53:12,400
Okay.

621
00:53:16,680 --> 00:53:19,256
Brother, look, you'll collapse right
where you are without even blinking.

622
00:53:19,280 --> 00:53:21,160
At least rest for half an hour.

623
00:53:21,240 --> 00:53:22,536
Catch your breath, pull yourself together.

624
00:53:22,560 --> 00:53:23,920
Burak and I will continue.

625
00:53:25,800 --> 00:53:27,000
Until Mercan is found, I can't

626
00:53:27,280 --> 00:53:28,280
sleep a single second.

627
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:32,440
Even the breath I take
without her is hard for me.

628
00:53:36,200 --> 00:53:38,000
I'll go get us some
coffee and be right back.

629
00:53:43,840 --> 00:53:46,240
We still haven't found
anything. Neither her nor a clue.

630
00:53:46,600 --> 00:53:48,720
As time passes, things are getting worse.

631
00:53:48,880 --> 00:53:50,560
We've put men everywhere she could go.

632
00:53:51,080 --> 00:53:52,576
We've already checked
everywhere she could be.

633
00:53:52,600 --> 00:53:55,016
She's not getting caught right
now simply because she's not moving.

634
00:53:55,040 --> 00:53:57,600
The slightest movement and
we'll be on her tail, don't worry.

635
00:54:01,240 --> 00:54:03,320
Demet has come to the
mansion. I'll go check on her.

636
00:54:08,760 --> 00:54:11,400
If anything happens to Mercan,
I'll never forgive myself.

637
00:54:12,640 --> 00:54:13,640
Never.

638
00:54:25,920 --> 00:54:29,520
Look, be a man for once in your life.

639
00:54:29,960 --> 00:54:31,320
Your business is with me.

640
00:54:31,880 --> 00:54:36,800
Let go of Mercan, I'll
come. Let's settle our scores.

641
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:39,400
I need to think about this.

642
00:54:40,080 --> 00:54:41,120
You're scared, aren't you?

643
00:54:42,080 --> 00:54:43,080
Of facing me.

644
00:54:43,640 --> 00:54:45,040
Don't think too highly of yourself.

645
00:54:45,920 --> 00:54:46,960
I'm holding all the cards.

646
00:54:47,400 --> 00:54:48,400
You're scared.

647
00:54:48,840 --> 00:54:49,840
What if I die?

648
00:54:50,520 --> 00:54:52,680
Otherwise, you would've faced me by now.

649
00:54:53,920 --> 00:54:54,200
Why would I be scared of you,

650
00:54:54,240 --> 00:54:55,240
huh?

651
00:54:56,440 --> 00:54:57,440
In a situation like this.

652
00:54:58,560 --> 00:55:01,080
You can only talk tough from a
distance, that's all you can do.

653
00:55:01,320 --> 00:55:03,000
Yiğit, come to the location I'll send you.

654
00:55:03,760 --> 00:55:04,760
But I have one condition.

655
00:55:05,240 --> 00:55:06,240
Tell me.

656
00:55:06,560 --> 00:55:07,600
You'll come alone.

657
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:16,120
If I see someone with you, or if I find out you called the
police—and you know I have long arms, I will find out...

658
00:55:17,160 --> 00:55:18,720
Then you'll never see Mercan again.

659
00:55:19,760 --> 00:55:20,760
I'll come alone.

660
00:55:21,800 --> 00:55:23,120
Don't you dare touch Mercan.

661
00:55:23,920 --> 00:55:24,920
Do you hear me?

662
00:55:51,200 --> 00:55:53,160
Listen, take someone else with you.

663
00:55:53,280 --> 00:55:54,840
Go to that old plot of land we have.

664
00:55:54,880 --> 00:55:55,880
Ateş will come there.

665
00:55:56,040 --> 00:55:57,096
Box him up and bring him to me.

666
00:55:57,120 --> 00:55:58,120
Yes, sir.

667
00:55:59,880 --> 00:56:00,880
Good. Be careful.

668
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:02,000
Alright.

669
00:56:12,480 --> 00:56:13,800
I'm so sorry, Cemal.

670
00:56:16,040 --> 00:56:18,520
I sink into the ground with
shame just thinking about it.

671
00:56:18,960 --> 00:56:21,360
How can he do something so
crazy? I don't understand.

672
00:56:23,320 --> 00:56:26,480
Demet, look, don't blame
yourself for his actions.

673
00:56:27,280 --> 00:56:28,280
He's a grown man.

674
00:56:28,960 --> 00:56:30,680
He should be able to tell right from wrong.

675
00:56:31,720 --> 00:56:33,560
If he can't, the sin
and the shame are on him.

676
00:56:33,600 --> 00:56:34,600
Not you.

677
00:56:36,160 --> 00:56:37,760
I'm so angry with myself.

678
00:56:39,040 --> 00:56:41,640
I called everywhere, everyone.

679
00:56:41,720 --> 00:56:44,240
But no one knows anything.

680
00:56:49,080 --> 00:56:50,680
You believe me, don't you, Cemal?

681
00:56:51,000 --> 00:56:52,400
I do, of course I do.

682
00:56:53,200 --> 00:56:54,440
I trust you, Demet.

683
00:56:55,560 --> 00:56:56,800
You're very different from him.

684
00:56:58,600 --> 00:56:59,600
Thanks.

685
00:57:00,320 --> 00:57:02,960
This means a lot to me.

686
00:57:06,600 --> 00:57:10,560
In fact, it's my only comfort
in this terrible situation.

687
00:57:17,200 --> 00:57:18,200
What are you doing here?

688
00:57:18,560 --> 00:57:21,880
I researched every record
on Nazir until morning.

689
00:57:22,440 --> 00:57:24,160
He recently bought a plot of land.

690
00:57:25,040 --> 00:57:27,200
If he hasn't taken Mercan
and fled immediately,

691
00:57:27,640 --> 00:57:28,760
he's still there.

692
00:57:30,560 --> 00:57:31,640
I know him.

693
00:57:32,520 --> 00:57:34,200
I think he'll set a trap for Ateş.

694
00:57:43,680 --> 00:57:46,560
Mr. Ateş just left like crazy. We
asked him, but he didn't say anything.

695
00:57:55,160 --> 00:57:56,160
Oh, for crying out loud.

696
00:57:56,840 --> 00:57:58,640
He must have already
lured him into the trap.

697
00:57:59,240 --> 00:58:00,320
Where is this plot of land?

698
00:58:02,560 --> 00:58:03,560
Alright.

699
00:58:03,960 --> 00:58:05,280
Send me the location immediately.

700
00:59:24,400 --> 00:59:28,000
But what... what is
this slipper doing here?

701
00:59:29,720 --> 00:59:33,000
What is it doing in Ms. Müzeyyen's room?

702
00:59:44,760 --> 00:59:45,760
Take this!

703
00:59:49,320 --> 00:59:51,560
This baby is now Nermin's and my baby.

704
00:59:56,240 --> 00:59:57,240
His name is Murat.

705
00:59:58,560 --> 00:59:59,640
Listen to me, Binnaz.

706
01:00:01,440 --> 01:00:03,840
This secret will go to
the grave with both of us.

707
01:00:03,880 --> 01:00:05,080
Do you understand?

708
01:00:09,960 --> 01:00:12,000
Come on, take this and
get it out of here, Nermine.

709
01:00:21,120 --> 01:00:24,240
God forbid. What is this
doing in Ms. Müzeyyen's room?

710
01:00:30,880 --> 01:00:32,160
What are you doing here?

711
01:00:34,480 --> 01:00:35,480
Why did you take this?

712
01:00:36,320 --> 01:00:39,280
I was cleaning, Ms. Müzeyyen.

713
01:00:40,280 --> 01:00:41,760
Don't you ever touch this again.

714
01:00:42,880 --> 01:00:44,960
This is the only thing
left from my deceased son.

715
01:00:46,200 --> 01:00:49,000
The only thing left from my
baby who died because of Haydar.

716
01:01:14,000 --> 01:01:16,040
Is there a pair for this, Ms. Müzeyyen?

717
01:01:17,720 --> 01:01:20,640
No. Why did you ask that?

718
01:01:22,920 --> 01:01:23,920
Okay.
No.

719
01:01:25,680 --> 01:01:26,680
I didn't ask anything.

720
01:01:26,880 --> 01:01:28,120
I didn't ask anything.

721
01:01:58,400 --> 01:01:59,720
Ateş will be around here soon.

722
01:02:00,560 --> 01:02:01,640
Spread out.

723
01:02:24,680 --> 01:02:25,760
Look. I brought it for you.

724
01:02:41,400 --> 01:02:42,400
Come on.

725
01:02:43,480 --> 01:02:44,480
Eat some.

726
01:02:47,760 --> 01:02:50,240
Look, let's make a deal.

727
01:02:52,360 --> 01:02:53,360
You eat this.

728
01:02:54,160 --> 01:02:55,640
And I'll hurt Ateş less.

729
01:02:57,160 --> 01:02:58,640
If you harm a single hair on Ateş,

730
01:02:59,120 --> 01:03:00,200
I won't let you live.

731
01:03:01,720 --> 01:03:03,000
Then you'll do what I want.

732
01:03:04,800 --> 01:03:05,800
Come on.

733
01:03:07,600 --> 01:03:07,920
Okay.

734
01:03:08,400 --> 01:03:10,000
Come on, eat. Okay, just don't hurt him.

735
01:03:27,160 --> 01:03:29,440
I knew we'd eventually
come to an agreement.

736
01:04:22,280 --> 01:04:23,280
Put your hands up.

737
01:04:25,680 --> 01:04:26,680
Where's Nezir?

738
01:04:28,680 --> 01:04:30,920
You'll see when we get
there. Get in the car.

739
01:04:44,400 --> 01:04:45,400
Ah!

740
01:04:51,480 --> 01:04:52,480
Where's Nezir?

741
01:04:57,240 --> 01:04:59,920
Where's Nezir?

742
01:05:06,040 --> 01:05:07,616
Come on, you're only taking a tiny bite.

743
01:05:07,640 --> 01:05:08,960
Bite it properly and finish it.

744
01:05:09,320 --> 01:05:10,560
I don't want to, that's enough.

745
01:05:12,480 --> 01:05:14,240
But you haven't eaten anything!

746
01:05:16,400 --> 01:05:18,440
I just want you to untie my hands, please!

747
01:05:20,200 --> 01:05:21,480
Not that much, Meryem.

748
01:05:22,760 --> 01:05:23,760
Slowly.

749
01:05:24,040 --> 01:05:26,080
I need to go to the restroom.

750
01:05:31,080 --> 01:05:32,080
Alright.

751
01:05:34,480 --> 01:05:36,240
But don't force me to use this.

752
01:05:59,280 --> 01:06:00,280
What did you do?

753
01:06:08,120 --> 01:06:09,320
What did you do to your hands?

754
01:06:13,520 --> 01:06:14,520
Okay, it'll pass.

755
01:06:15,600 --> 01:06:16,600
It'll pass.

756
01:06:17,920 --> 01:06:19,760
We'll laugh at all these
memories. It'll pass.

757
01:06:41,760 --> 01:06:42,760
Mercan!

758
01:06:43,880 --> 01:06:46,080
The only thing I'll remember
is your disgustingness.

759
01:06:46,760 --> 01:06:48,720
And this will be the last
thing you remember too.

760
01:06:49,320 --> 01:06:50,960
Mercan!

761
01:06:51,480 --> 01:06:52,480
Ah!

762
01:07:10,360 --> 01:07:11,360
You can't go anywhere.

763
01:07:16,760 --> 01:07:17,240
Do you understand?

764
01:07:17,640 --> 01:07:18,640
What the hell...

765
01:07:18,840 --> 01:07:19,920
Nazir

766
01:07:20,440 --> 01:07:22,240
Don't you see what state we're in?

767
01:07:34,160 --> 01:07:35,520
Why did you do this to me?

768
01:07:36,760 --> 01:07:37,760
You?

769
01:07:42,640 --> 01:07:44,040
You're sad too, aren't you?

770
01:07:44,600 --> 01:07:45,600
Don't be sad.

771
01:07:47,080 --> 01:07:48,320
I know you love me too.

772
01:07:49,880 --> 01:07:51,640
Look.

773
01:07:53,640 --> 01:07:54,640
All covered in blood

774
01:07:56,520 --> 01:07:57,720
I told you I don't love you.

775
01:07:57,840 --> 01:07:59,320
I don't love you, understand already.

776
01:07:59,400 --> 01:08:02,880
You do! You do! You do! You do! You do!

777
01:08:03,560 --> 01:08:04,680
You do!

778
01:08:55,320 --> 01:08:56,320
Did I hurt you?

779
01:08:58,240 --> 01:08:59,480
I don’t want to hurt you.

780
01:09:01,000 --> 01:09:02,000
I’m sorry.

781
01:09:02,360 --> 01:09:03,400
Would I ever hurt you?

782
01:09:05,280 --> 01:09:07,680
I have no mother, no father.

783
01:09:10,600 --> 01:09:11,600
Only one sister.

784
01:09:13,000 --> 01:09:14,000
And you.

785
01:09:15,560 --> 01:09:18,040
I have taken refuge in
your love all this time.

786
01:09:24,760 --> 01:09:25,600
Mercan…

787
01:09:25,601 --> 01:09:27,200
…I love you so much.

788
01:09:28,160 --> 01:09:29,919
I love you more than anything.

789
01:09:29,920 --> 01:09:32,120
No one can love you the way I do.

790
01:09:34,080 --> 01:09:35,080
That Ateş…

791
01:09:35,280 --> 01:09:36,920
…thinks he loves you.

792
01:09:39,080 --> 01:09:40,200
But he’s wrong.

793
01:09:41,800 --> 01:09:43,440
Poor thing.

794
01:09:44,880 --> 01:09:46,160
He only suffers from afar, see.

795
01:09:48,400 --> 01:09:49,799
I…

796
01:09:49,800 --> 01:09:50,800
…what about me?

797
01:09:51,840 --> 01:09:54,400
I’m in your mind.

798
01:09:56,520 --> 01:09:57,520
I’m in your soul.

799
01:09:58,480 --> 01:09:59,879
Look…

800
01:09:59,880 --> 01:10:00,560
…see…

801
01:10:00,880 --> 01:10:02,879
I’m always…

802
01:10:02,880 --> 01:10:03,880
No!

803
01:10:04,160 --> 01:10:06,360
No!

804
01:10:07,520 --> 01:10:11,080
No! No! No! No!

805
01:10:12,160 --> 01:10:13,160
No!

806
01:10:13,720 --> 01:10:14,720
No!

807
01:10:29,240 --> 01:10:30,240
Don’t say it!

808
01:10:32,080 --> 01:10:33,120
Don’t say it!

809
01:10:38,960 --> 01:10:39,960
Look at me.

810
01:10:40,880 --> 01:10:41,880
Look at me.

811
01:10:41,960 --> 01:10:42,960
Look into my eyes.

812
01:10:44,640 --> 01:10:45,160
Mercan!

813
01:10:45,360 --> 01:10:46,360
Look into my eyes.

814
01:10:47,520 --> 01:10:48,520
What do you see?
Huh?

815
01:10:50,760 --> 01:10:51,760
Just an ordinary person?

816
01:10:55,360 --> 01:10:56,360
No.

817
01:10:57,720 --> 01:10:59,440
I’m not an ordinary person.

818
01:11:00,120 --> 01:11:01,840
You know this very well. I am you.

819
01:11:04,000 --> 01:11:05,200
And you are me.

820
01:11:08,040 --> 01:11:08,560
Every step you take…

821
01:11:09,000 --> 01:11:11,120
…I am the sound of it, Mercan.

822
01:11:12,640 --> 01:11:13,320
You…

823
01:11:13,321 --> 01:11:14,360
At night…

824
01:11:15,120 --> 01:11:16,120
Listen to me.

825
01:11:17,360 --> 01:11:20,720
There are nightmares that
enter your dreams. I am that too.

826
01:11:22,240 --> 01:11:23,480
I am everything to you.

827
01:11:26,600 --> 01:11:27,920
For you…

828
01:11:29,280 --> 01:11:30,760
…I would even face death…

829
01:11:32,840 --> 01:11:34,199
…I would kill…

830
01:11:34,200 --> 01:11:36,040
…I would do anything for you.

831
01:11:37,040 --> 01:11:38,040
Do you understand?

832
01:11:38,480 --> 01:11:39,480
Huh?

833
01:11:39,880 --> 01:11:41,280
Can your beautiful mind grasp this?

834
01:11:41,440 --> 01:11:42,440
Huh?

835
01:11:45,680 --> 01:11:46,719
You…

836
01:11:46,720 --> 01:11:49,040
You’ve lost your mind. You’ve gone crazy.

837
01:11:49,840 --> 01:11:50,840
Go away.

838
01:12:20,680 --> 01:12:21,680
Mercan…

839
01:12:21,720 --> 01:12:22,840
…you are mine…

840
01:12:25,360 --> 01:12:26,360
Understand this already.

841
01:12:30,040 --> 01:12:31,280
You belong to me.

842
01:12:31,800 --> 01:12:32,800
Only to me!

843
01:12:35,640 --> 01:12:36,640
Do you understand?

844
01:12:37,560 --> 01:12:38,880
I said don’t.

845
01:12:40,240 --> 01:12:41,240
Please.

846
01:12:44,880 --> 01:12:46,240
I beg you, please.

847
01:12:49,200 --> 01:12:51,080
I haven’t done anything.

848
01:12:53,640 --> 01:12:55,280
I only loved you.

849
01:12:56,440 --> 01:12:58,480
I loved you to death, loved you like crazy.

850
01:13:05,480 --> 01:13:07,520
But now I don’t even
care if you don’t love me.

851
01:13:08,960 --> 01:13:10,120
I never cared, in fact.

852
01:13:12,480 --> 01:13:14,680
I burned my bridges, girl.

853
01:13:21,440 --> 01:13:23,120
Since you’re not here…

854
01:13:29,840 --> 01:13:33,959
Since we can’t meet in this life…

855
01:13:33,960 --> 01:13:36,600
We’ll be together in another life.

856
01:13:37,880 --> 01:13:38,720
Nezir…

857
01:13:38,721 --> 01:13:39,760
…look, please, don’t.

858
01:13:41,240 --> 01:13:44,000
You… you’ll find someone to love you.

859
01:13:44,440 --> 01:13:45,120
And they will love you deeply.

860
01:13:45,160 --> 01:13:47,200
You’ll love them deeply too.

861
01:13:47,440 --> 01:13:48,920
Look, please, pull yourself together.

862
01:13:49,520 --> 01:13:50,520
Nezir…
Shut up!

863
01:13:51,920 --> 01:13:52,920
Shut up!

864
01:13:53,200 --> 01:13:54,200
Shut up!

865
01:13:55,240 --> 01:13:57,200
There won’t be anyone else!

866
01:13:59,200 --> 01:14:00,960
Understand this, there
won’t be anyone else.

867
01:14:04,800 --> 01:14:05,960
There won’t be anyone else.

868
01:14:12,560 --> 01:14:13,560
Or wait…

869
01:14:19,560 --> 01:14:21,239
Or…

870
01:14:21,240 --> 01:14:22,560
…first I’ll shoot you.

871
01:14:25,040 --> 01:14:26,840
Then I’ll take care of myself anyway.

872
01:14:31,720 --> 01:14:32,560
But…

873
01:14:32,561 --> 01:14:34,160
…I can’t bring myself to hurt you.

874
01:14:59,600 --> 01:15:02,960
But if I die first…

875
01:15:04,040 --> 01:15:06,400
…this time you’ll be with Ateş.

876
01:15:22,640 --> 01:15:24,560
Nezir, don’t do this.

877
01:15:27,240 --> 01:15:28,640
Mercan?

878
01:15:34,320 --> 01:15:35,320
No!

879
01:15:49,880 --> 01:15:50,880
Mercan!

880
01:15:58,760 --> 01:15:59,760
Mercan!

881
01:16:40,800 --> 01:16:41,800
Thank god! Ateş

882
01:16:42,800 --> 01:16:44,799
Mercan, Mercan!!

883
01:16:44,800 --> 01:16:47,800
Are you Okay? You are okay right?

884
01:16:48,800 --> 01:16:49,800
I am fine

885
01:17:09,800 --> 01:17:10,800
Ateş, Ateş

886
01:17:37,800 --> 01:17:38,800
Ateş!

887
01:17:49,120 --> 01:17:50,120
Ateş!

888
01:17:53,400 --> 01:17:56,200
You’re okay, right Mercan? He
didn’t do anything to you, did he?

889
01:17:57,000 --> 01:17:58,000
Tell me the truth.

890
01:17:58,400 --> 01:17:59,400
I’m fine.

891
01:17:59,480 --> 01:18:01,320
Tell me the truth, he
didn’t hurt you, did he?

892
01:18:01,880 --> 01:18:04,200
No, no, I’m really fine.

893
01:18:05,280 --> 01:18:07,200
He’s the one who got hurt the most anyway.

894
01:18:11,480 --> 01:18:15,640
My brave wife. I’ll kill him,
you hear me? I’ll kill him.

895
01:18:16,240 --> 01:18:17,880
He will never be able to hurt you again.

896
01:18:27,480 --> 01:18:29,600
You check upstairs, you
check downstairs. Be careful.

897
01:18:30,320 --> 01:18:31,320
Ateş, are you okay?

898
01:18:32,280 --> 01:18:34,600
We’re fine. The bastard got away.

899
01:19:01,680 --> 01:19:05,680
Hey Ateş Karahan! This isn’t over!

900
01:19:11,480 --> 01:19:13,720
Move. Get out.

901
01:19:22,400 --> 01:19:24,120
No one’s here.

902
01:19:25,000 --> 01:19:27,000
Looks like they escaped
once Mercan got free.

903
01:19:29,120 --> 01:19:33,320
If he thinks he can get away, he’s wrong. Even
if he crawls into a snake hole, I’ll find him.

904
01:19:35,000 --> 01:19:40,840
He’s planning to flee abroad. He
got a passport. He even got one for me.

905
01:19:42,600 --> 01:19:43,600
Let’s go.

906
01:19:45,160 --> 01:19:48,000
Cemal, burn this place down.

907
01:19:50,560 --> 01:19:54,040
Don’t leave a single stone
standing in a place that scared Mercan.

908
01:20:26,200 --> 01:20:27,920
Here, my dear.

909
01:20:30,480 --> 01:20:34,080
Mom, are you okay?

910
01:20:37,680 --> 01:20:38,800
I’m not, my girl.

911
01:20:39,760 --> 01:20:42,560
How can anyone be okay after all this?

912
01:20:47,360 --> 01:20:51,200
Insallah nothing will happen.
Aunt Binnaz, don’t upset yourself.

913
01:20:52,840 --> 01:20:53,840
Insallah.

914
01:20:54,520 --> 01:20:56,480
I hope Ateş Bey finds her, but...

915
01:20:57,880 --> 01:21:02,120
These kidnapping cases
don’t usually end well.

916
01:21:03,760 --> 01:21:07,919
Berat, son, don’t talk
like that and bring bad luck.

917
01:21:07,920 --> 01:21:11,720
Brother, yeah, don’t jinx it.

918
01:21:15,080 --> 01:21:18,120
What am I supposed to do? I don’t
even know what to think anymore.

919
01:21:19,080 --> 01:21:20,920
Stuff like this doesn’t
even happen in movies.

920
01:21:23,040 --> 01:21:27,800
Honestly, I feel at ease. I’m
sure Ateş Bey will find his wife.

921
01:21:28,040 --> 01:21:31,160
He’ll bring her back safe and
sound. That’s why I’m calm.

922
01:21:33,600 --> 01:21:35,280
Mrs. Mercan has been found.

923
01:21:36,640 --> 01:21:39,080
My God, thank you. Thank you.

924
01:21:40,680 --> 01:21:42,919
Look, thank God, my dear.

925
01:21:42,920 --> 01:21:45,160
See, I told you. Brother-in-law, you see?

926
01:21:46,000 --> 01:21:47,320
My expert brother-in-law.

927
01:21:49,200 --> 01:21:49,640
Congratulations.

928
01:21:50,120 --> 01:21:51,120
Thanks, brother-in-law.

929
01:21:53,920 --> 01:21:56,560
Oh thank God. See, it’s all sorted now.

930
01:21:56,840 --> 01:21:58,240
Thank God. Thank God.

931
01:22:24,600 --> 01:22:26,000
My daughter.

932
01:22:28,240 --> 01:22:29,640
My dear.

933
01:22:37,640 --> 01:22:41,640
I died and came back to life, I swear.
You’re okay, right? I was so scared.

934
01:22:56,080 --> 01:22:58,800
I’m fine, Mom, I’m fine. Please don’t cry.

935
01:23:01,360 --> 01:23:02,520
You brought my daughter back.

936
01:23:02,760 --> 01:23:04,960
Thank you so much.

937
01:23:08,200 --> 01:23:09,200
Mercan.

938
01:23:17,120 --> 01:23:19,200
Burak, Burak.

939
01:23:22,600 --> 01:23:25,080
If you squeezed a little harder,
you would’ve broken my bones.

940
01:23:25,360 --> 01:23:29,480
I’m so sorry, Mercan. I
was really worried about you.

941
01:23:30,000 --> 01:23:31,200
You mean a lot to me.

942
01:23:32,200 --> 01:23:33,440
You mean a lot to me too.

943
01:23:37,320 --> 01:23:38,800
Ateş brother.

944
01:23:40,080 --> 01:23:43,240
Thank you so much for bringing
my sister back safe and sound.

945
01:23:58,960 --> 01:23:59,960
Get well soon.

946
01:24:00,240 --> 01:24:01,240
Get well soon.

947
01:24:17,360 --> 01:24:18,800
I was just about to see Aslı off.

948
01:24:32,720 --> 01:24:34,280
I’m so sorry, Mercan.

949
01:24:35,280 --> 01:24:38,480
I don’t even know what
to say. I’m so ashamed.

950
01:24:39,480 --> 01:24:40,600
Please forgive me.

951
01:24:43,440 --> 01:24:46,680
It’s not your fault. Don’t blame yourself.

952
01:24:47,560 --> 01:24:53,080
Yes, but he’s my brother. I should have
realized he would do something like this.

953
01:25:06,520 --> 01:25:09,000
If anything had happened to
you, I would never forgive myself.

954
01:25:14,440 --> 01:25:15,440
Mercan.

955
01:25:17,600 --> 01:25:19,680
You need to rest. Come on.

956
01:25:36,880 --> 01:25:38,200
I should get going.

957
01:25:38,680 --> 01:25:42,520
Stay a bit longer. I need to talk
to Ateş. Then I’ll drop you off.

958
01:25:44,440 --> 01:25:45,880
Okay. I’ll be outside.

959
01:25:50,240 --> 01:25:53,800
You wanted this girl dead.
Why did you help find her?

960
01:25:57,440 --> 01:25:59,680
Or are you still up to something, Aslı?

961
01:26:01,400 --> 01:26:04,560
Don’t be ridiculous,
Mom. What would I be up to?

962
01:26:06,680 --> 01:26:08,880
Everything I’ve done
so far was wrong anyway.

963
01:26:11,440 --> 01:26:12,920
I hurt Ateş a lot.

964
01:26:13,840 --> 01:26:15,880
I don’t want to hurt him anymore.

965
01:26:20,680 --> 01:26:22,080
I turned this mansion into hell.

966
01:26:24,320 --> 01:26:27,240
I won’t do anything to
overshadow Ateş’s life anymore.

967
01:26:29,320 --> 01:26:30,720
Maybe one day he’ll forgive me.

968
01:26:36,240 --> 01:26:41,040
Well done, my girl. I knew
you’d pull yourself together.

969
01:26:54,600 --> 01:26:57,720
From now on I’ll learn
from my mistakes and move on.

970
01:26:59,560 --> 01:27:00,560
Alright then.

971
01:27:31,000 --> 01:27:32,160
Oh my God.

972
01:27:35,000 --> 01:27:37,240
What now? You’re going too far.

973
01:27:55,200 --> 01:27:56,200
Thank God.

974
01:28:00,160 --> 01:28:02,520
I’m safe in my home again.

975
01:28:05,760 --> 01:28:09,000
You’re home. You’re with me, thank God.

976
01:28:19,800 --> 01:28:20,560
Let’s dress your wounds right away.

977
01:28:20,561 --> 01:28:21,960
I’m fine.

978
01:28:26,040 --> 01:28:28,840
Really, don’t worry. I’m fine.

979
01:28:30,040 --> 01:28:31,240
Let me take a shower first.

980
01:28:35,440 --> 01:28:42,280
As you wish. I’m so
sorry all this happened.

981
01:28:43,960 --> 01:28:46,360
I shouldn’t have left you alone.

982
01:28:49,600 --> 01:28:55,920
Don’t blame yourself. I knew
you’d find me. You always do.

983
01:29:04,160 --> 01:29:07,880
I will never leave you
alone again. I promise.

984
01:29:11,680 --> 01:29:12,720
I’ll be more careful.

985
01:29:20,040 --> 01:29:26,120
Get some rest. Take a shower. I’ll
talk to Cemal and come right back.

986
01:29:27,760 --> 01:29:29,919
Do you want anything? You must be hungry.

987
01:29:29,920 --> 01:29:32,656
I’ll have something prepared for you. What
should I make? I’ll have them cook it right away.

988
01:29:32,680 --> 01:29:36,920
No. Don’t make anything. I don’t
want anything. I just want to rest.

989
01:29:42,880 --> 01:29:49,840
Ateş, Nezir has lost his mind.
There’s no telling what he might do.

990
01:29:54,840 --> 01:30:02,840
If anything happens to you, I won’t be able to bear
it. Don’t go after him. Let the police handle it.

991
01:30:07,000 --> 01:30:15,000
He can’t do anything to
you or me. I won’t allow it.

992
01:31:41,680 --> 01:31:47,680
You know those nightmares that haunt you
at night? That’s me. I am your everything.

993
01:31:50,520 --> 01:31:56,600
For you, I’d risk death… even killing.

994
01:31:58,440 --> 01:32:04,239
If we can’t be together in
this life… we will be in another.

995
01:32:04,240 --> 01:32:06,640
There will be no one else.

996
01:32:08,720 --> 01:32:10,520
Do you understand?
There will be no one else.

997
01:32:12,720 --> 01:32:13,720
No.

998
01:32:39,040 --> 01:32:40,600
Get out of my head.

999
01:32:41,560 --> 01:32:43,800
Your daughter’s been found.
What’s all this anger about?

1000
01:32:46,560 --> 01:32:51,720
Mashallah, your daughter has nine
lives. She gets out of every disaster.

1001
01:32:53,760 --> 01:32:57,560
I knew you were putting on
an act. Those half-hearted

1002
01:32:57,600 --> 01:33:01,640
“get well soon” wishes, pretending to help.

1003
01:33:03,560 --> 01:33:07,320
Ateş might fall for your act. But I won’t.

1004
01:33:08,600 --> 01:33:11,040
I don’t care what you think about me.

1005
01:33:14,360 --> 01:33:17,560
You and your murderer daughter will
get what’s coming to you one day.

1006
01:33:19,560 --> 01:33:27,560
Divine justice never fails, Mrs. Müzeyyen.
Sooner or later, you’ll suffer too.

1007
01:33:31,440 --> 01:33:33,199
If you call my daughter a murderer again…

1008
01:33:33,200 --> 01:33:36,399
A murderer is called a murderer.

1009
01:33:36,400 --> 01:33:40,320
Your daughter is a murderer.
Your daughter is a murderer.

1010
01:33:42,240 --> 01:33:45,520
So I live to hear this from
someone whose son is a killer.

1011
01:33:47,360 --> 01:33:49,920
My son always tried to be good.

1012
01:33:51,560 --> 01:33:54,720
He killed someone by accident,
but he was ready to pay the price.

1013
01:33:56,000 --> 01:34:00,880
And your daughter? She’s
still walking around shamelessly.

1014
01:34:02,120 --> 01:34:09,840
Your son got what he
deserved. Bad seed. I can tell.

1015
01:34:11,560 --> 01:34:16,920
Bad seed? Murat was not worse
than you and your murderer daughter.

1016
01:34:20,800 --> 01:34:23,080
If you call my daughter a
murderer again, I’ll kill you.

1017
01:34:23,840 --> 01:34:31,840
Your daughter is a killer just like
you. You sent my son to the grave.

1018
01:34:38,720 --> 01:34:40,600
You’ll get what’s coming
to you, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

1019
01:34:56,480 --> 01:35:00,120
This secret has chained itself to my feet.

1020
01:35:00,960 --> 01:35:04,520
While I was struggling with how to tell
Mrs. Nermin, now Mrs. Müzeyyen appeared too.

1021
01:35:05,520 --> 01:35:09,840
If I say one word, it will turn into a
bloodbath. They already hate each other.

1022
01:35:18,800 --> 01:35:20,240
Mom.

1023
01:35:26,600 --> 01:35:28,600
Are you okay?

1024
01:35:30,120 --> 01:35:34,880
What’s wrong, Mom? You’ve been
wandering around absent-minded all day.

1025
01:35:37,240 --> 01:35:38,520
Tell us.

1026
01:35:41,080 --> 01:35:45,120
Çiçek, stop asking me if I’m okay
all the time. I’m fine, alright?

1027
01:35:50,040 --> 01:35:54,920
Dinner isn’t ready yet, that’s what’s
bothering me. You two take care of things here.

1028
01:35:56,880 --> 01:36:04,880
Mom, the soup… Mom?

1029
01:36:05,160 --> 01:36:06,520
She’s hiding something from us.

1030
01:36:08,280 --> 01:36:09,720
She is, it’s obvious.

1031
01:36:11,560 --> 01:36:13,400
What could she be hiding?

1032
01:36:21,120 --> 01:36:26,600
What if we hadn’t found her?
What if Nezir had hurt her?

1033
01:36:29,720 --> 01:36:31,240
I go crazy just thinking about it.

1034
01:36:35,160 --> 01:36:37,120
When I found Mercan, she
was trembling with fear.

1035
01:36:40,120 --> 01:36:44,920
I can’t bear even a single
tear falling from her eyes.

1036
01:36:46,040 --> 01:36:48,720
You’re right, brother. What can I
even say? There’s nothing to say.

1037
01:36:49,160 --> 01:36:51,640
We’ve been through a lot lately.

1038
01:36:52,160 --> 01:36:55,560
If it were someone else in her place,
I don’t know if they could handle it.

1039
01:36:56,000 --> 01:36:59,560
I’m at fault too. I couldn’t
protect her from Nezir or from Aslı.

1040
01:37:00,680 --> 01:37:04,160
Those kinds of devilish schemes aren’t easy
to deal with. Not everyone can handle them.

1041
01:37:09,200 --> 01:37:10,200
Aslı.

1042
01:37:12,480 --> 01:37:15,040
Aslı told us Nezir had
a plot of land there.

1043
01:37:17,040 --> 01:37:20,920
She looked into Nezir. She
guessed he took Mercan there.

1044
01:37:22,000 --> 01:37:25,400
You had already gone,
but it still surprised me.

1045
01:37:33,280 --> 01:37:34,880
It’s hard for me to trust Aslı anymore.

1046
01:37:38,160 --> 01:37:39,320
We need to catch Nezir.

1047
01:37:41,760 --> 01:37:43,440
Mercan’s safety is at stake.

1048
01:37:44,160 --> 01:37:47,720
Don’t worry, brother. What have
we ever set our minds to and failed?

1049
01:37:48,080 --> 01:37:49,560
The police are already after him too.

1050
01:37:50,080 --> 01:37:52,016
Let him run as much as he
wants. How far can he go?

1051
01:37:52,040 --> 01:37:53,240
He won’t run forever.

1052
01:37:53,840 --> 01:37:55,920
One day, he’ll either
surrender or we’ll catch him.

1053
01:37:57,920 --> 01:37:59,120
You leave Nezir aside for now.

1054
01:38:00,560 --> 01:38:01,560
Focus on Mercan.

1055
01:38:02,400 --> 01:38:04,880
She’s come back from the brink
of death too many times lately.

1056
01:38:05,200 --> 01:38:07,720
She’s not in a good mental
state. You need to lift her spirits.

1057
01:38:07,880 --> 01:38:08,880
Leave Nezir to me.

1058
01:38:11,360 --> 01:38:14,800
How will I ever repay you, Cemal?

1059
01:38:16,160 --> 01:38:20,240
All this time, you’ve carried my
troubles as if they were your own.

1060
01:38:21,240 --> 01:38:24,440
Come on, aren’t we brothers? If it were
the other way around, you’d do the same.

1061
01:38:27,480 --> 01:38:32,240
Don’t let what Nezir did
come between you and Demet.

1062
01:38:33,800 --> 01:38:35,599
I’ve told you this before.

1063
01:38:35,600 --> 01:38:39,600
Demet and I are just two
friends who get along well.

1064
01:38:45,280 --> 01:38:49,600
I need to drop Demet off. If
you’ll excuse me, I’ll be right back.

1065
01:39:02,280 --> 01:39:04,079
I was just about to call you.

1066
01:39:04,080 --> 01:39:07,280
Sorry, things took longer than I expected.

1067
01:39:08,080 --> 01:39:11,320
No problem. I was talking to Aunt Nermin.

1068
01:39:13,240 --> 01:39:14,440
I love her like my own mother.

1069
01:39:16,040 --> 01:39:17,840
I couldn’t stand being
on bad terms with her.

1070
01:39:18,920 --> 01:39:22,240
Blaming you for everything
that happened is very unfair.

1071
01:39:23,000 --> 01:39:27,040
Don’t say that. Anyone
in her place would be angry.

1072
01:39:29,280 --> 01:39:30,880
Thankfully, we talked and sorted it out.

1073
01:39:31,480 --> 01:39:32,520
That’s good then.

1074
01:39:33,480 --> 01:39:35,320
What about Mercan? Did
you get to talk to her?

1075
01:39:35,800 --> 01:39:37,520
I didn’t want to disturb her.

1076
01:39:39,840 --> 01:39:43,800
You saw her when she arrived,
she doesn’t blame anyone.

1077
01:39:45,960 --> 01:39:47,680
She doesn’t judge easily.

1078
01:39:48,840 --> 01:39:50,000
She keeps everything inside.

1079
01:39:51,680 --> 01:39:55,680
We can’t even imagine how
much pain she’s in right now.

1080
01:39:59,240 --> 01:40:01,360
But I should have realized, Cemal.

1081
01:40:04,160 --> 01:40:05,880
I should have understood.

1082
01:40:08,560 --> 01:40:10,279
But I…

1083
01:40:10,280 --> 01:40:11,600
I have no one else but him.

1084
01:40:20,440 --> 01:40:21,720
My brother…

1085
01:40:25,120 --> 01:40:26,360
My brother is not a bad person.

1086
01:40:30,440 --> 01:40:31,960
It’s always been because of my father.

1087
01:40:33,800 --> 01:40:35,520
He raised him that way.

1088
01:40:36,520 --> 01:40:40,040
He taught him he could take
anything he wanted by force.

1089
01:40:44,160 --> 01:40:45,960
Because that’s what a
man is supposed to be.

1090
01:40:49,600 --> 01:40:54,800
Since I was a girl, he
never spent time with me.

1091
01:40:57,400 --> 01:41:00,600
It was always my brother.

1092
01:41:02,320 --> 01:41:06,480
Still, none of this
justifies what happened.

1093
01:41:06,720 --> 01:41:07,720
Demet…

1094
01:41:24,040 --> 01:41:25,920
I don’t want to lose her.

1095
01:41:36,240 --> 01:41:38,600
But I can’t tolerate her injustices either.

1096
01:41:48,400 --> 01:41:49,760
I’m sorry.

1097
01:41:50,560 --> 01:41:51,560
It’s okay.

1098
01:41:53,920 --> 01:41:54,920
Shall we go?

1099
01:41:56,720 --> 01:41:58,440
I feel like I’m troubling you.

1100
01:41:58,920 --> 01:42:00,920
Not at all. Come on, let’s go.

1101
01:42:57,680 --> 01:43:00,120
Come, sit.

1102
01:44:13,120 --> 01:44:14,280
Thank you.

1103
01:44:15,040 --> 01:44:16,040
Do you feel better?

1104
01:44:17,440 --> 01:44:18,440
I’m fine.

1105
01:44:19,360 --> 01:44:23,000
How could I feel bad when I’m with you?

1106
01:44:29,400 --> 01:44:30,400
Does it hurt?

1107
01:44:32,600 --> 01:44:34,080
A little, not much.

1108
01:44:57,600 --> 01:44:58,600
Does this help?

1109
01:45:00,680 --> 01:45:02,440
Are you always going
to pamper me like this?

1110
01:45:04,280 --> 01:45:05,560
Of course.

1111
01:45:08,760 --> 01:45:10,000
I might become a burden though.

1112
01:45:11,360 --> 01:45:13,320
You think you’re not already one?

1113
01:45:14,720 --> 01:45:15,720
Oh, is that so?

1114
01:45:16,320 --> 01:45:17,560
Your hand’s a bit heavy though.

1115
01:45:18,160 --> 01:45:20,600
Since I’m already a burden,
I thought I’d live up to it.

1116
01:45:35,560 --> 01:45:37,440
You’re my sweet trouble.

1117
01:45:40,240 --> 01:45:41,240
And you’re mine.

1118
01:45:44,560 --> 01:45:46,800
I promise, I’ll always
be your sweet trouble.

1119
01:45:52,800 --> 01:45:54,720
May God never take you away from me.

1120
01:45:55,600 --> 01:45:56,600
Amen.

1121
01:46:03,480 --> 01:46:05,360
It’s always because of you.

1122
01:46:07,480 --> 01:46:09,919
The way you look at me…

1123
01:46:09,920 --> 01:46:12,040
Something happens in my heart.

1124
01:46:16,240 --> 01:46:17,760
I get emotional all the time.

1125
01:46:18,080 --> 01:46:19,600
And then my eyes fill with tears.

1126
01:46:20,640 --> 01:46:22,160
I’ll always look at you like this.

1127
01:46:25,440 --> 01:46:27,200
I prepared a surprise
for you in the garden.

1128
01:46:27,800 --> 01:46:28,800
What kind of surprise?

1129
01:46:45,560 --> 01:46:47,680
If you want to find
out, you’ll come with me.

1130
01:46:47,960 --> 01:46:48,960
Put this on.

1131
01:46:50,240 --> 01:46:50,800
Wear that too.

1132
01:46:50,960 --> 01:46:51,960
What’s going on?

1133
01:46:53,600 --> 01:46:55,400
You’ll see when we get there.

1134
01:46:56,640 --> 01:46:57,640
Come here.

1135
01:46:59,880 --> 01:47:01,280
Let’s wrap this one up like this.

1136
01:47:05,720 --> 01:47:06,960
Here, take it.
What’s happening?

1137
01:47:07,520 --> 01:47:08,520
What are you doing?

1138
01:47:09,080 --> 01:47:10,080
I don’t understand.

1139
01:47:10,720 --> 01:47:12,400
You turned me into a snowman again.

1140
01:47:12,640 --> 01:47:13,240
Yes, it worked.

1141
01:47:13,560 --> 01:47:14,920
Come on, come with me.

1142
01:47:21,960 --> 01:47:22,560
Ateş?

1143
01:47:22,760 --> 01:47:24,920
Why are you covering my eyes?

1144
01:47:25,480 --> 01:47:27,120
I said it’s a surprise.

1145
01:47:31,120 --> 01:47:31,760
Ateş.

1146
01:47:32,000 --> 01:47:33,000
Be patient.

1147
01:47:52,520 --> 01:47:53,520
Come.
Ateş.

1148
01:47:54,480 --> 01:47:55,480
Don’t be cold.

1149
01:48:02,480 --> 01:48:04,160
Very nice.

1150
01:48:26,720 --> 01:48:27,720
Do you remember?

1151
01:48:29,200 --> 01:48:30,760
One time, it snowed a lot.

1152
01:48:30,840 --> 01:48:33,720
But they didn’t let you go
outside because you might get sick.

1153
01:48:33,800 --> 01:48:37,240
I secretly brought you snowballs.

1154
01:51:39,840 --> 01:51:43,079
We need to find Nezir as soon as possible.

1155
01:51:43,080 --> 01:51:46,080
Otherwise, I won’t feel at ease.

1156
01:51:48,040 --> 01:51:50,360
Do you think Nezir could
contact Demet, what do you think?

1157
01:51:50,480 --> 01:51:51,560
He could, it’s possible.

1158
01:51:56,080 --> 01:51:57,800
Do you think Demet would tell us?

1159
01:52:00,760 --> 01:52:01,760
She could.

1160
01:52:04,480 --> 01:52:06,160
We talked a little yesterday, Demet and I.

1161
01:52:06,520 --> 01:52:08,280
She’s very upset about
what her brother did.

1162
01:52:09,000 --> 01:52:10,080
Demet is a good girl.

1163
01:52:11,520 --> 01:52:12,920
I know she’s upset.

1164
01:52:13,720 --> 01:52:16,440
But Nezir is her only
relative in this world.

1165
01:52:17,640 --> 01:52:21,560
If she has to choose a side, I
think she’ll take Mercan’s side.

1166
01:52:23,280 --> 01:52:24,840
Still, don’t trust her too much.

1167
01:52:25,000 --> 01:52:26,520
As I said, he’s her brother after all.

1168
01:52:28,960 --> 01:52:32,760
And even if Nezir is a nasty person,
his relationship with his sister is good.

1169
01:52:35,320 --> 01:52:38,000
Nezir also knows how much
his sister cares for him.

1170
01:52:38,640 --> 01:52:41,240
That’s why he can manipulate Demet easily.

1171
01:52:43,280 --> 01:52:46,320
The only thing he can’t handle
is if something happens to Demet.

1172
01:52:47,440 --> 01:52:48,600
Right, you’re correct.

1173
01:52:49,520 --> 01:52:51,520
I’ll do some investigating,
then we’ll talk again.

1174
01:53:46,000 --> 01:53:48,160
Follow the arrows.

1175
01:54:25,520 --> 01:54:26,600
Sit down, please.

1176
01:54:36,800 --> 01:54:38,360
Good morning, my dear.

1177
01:54:39,920 --> 01:54:41,000
Good morning.

1178
01:54:41,520 --> 01:54:44,040
Ateş, you’re spoiling me.

1179
01:54:44,640 --> 01:54:46,919
Surprise before sleeping,
surprise when waking up.

1180
01:54:46,920 --> 01:54:48,920
Don’t get me used to these things.

1181
01:54:51,960 --> 01:54:53,160
I’m used to it, my dear.

1182
01:54:53,600 --> 01:54:55,680
Aren’t you already spoiled?

1183
01:54:57,160 --> 01:54:58,240
Look now.

1184
01:54:59,720 --> 01:55:01,120
You’re my spoiled one.

1185
01:55:01,440 --> 01:55:03,200
You’re my pearl Mercan.

1186
01:55:07,800 --> 01:55:10,400
The excitement in your eyes…

1187
01:55:11,080 --> 01:55:12,320
That alone is worth everything.

1188
01:55:14,840 --> 01:55:16,440
Come on.

1189
01:55:26,200 --> 01:55:28,240
I know you didn’t sleep all night.

1190
01:55:29,480 --> 01:55:31,160
You were waiting for me, right?

1191
01:55:33,320 --> 01:55:35,120
It’s more accurate to
say I was watching you.

1192
01:55:36,720 --> 01:55:39,520
But again, you stayed awake because of me.

1193
01:55:41,600 --> 01:55:43,720
But you’re here in front of me.

1194
01:55:47,280 --> 01:55:50,680
I’d stay awake all night for you.

1195
01:56:07,880 --> 01:56:09,280
I love the way your face blushes.

1196
01:56:12,480 --> 01:56:13,480
Alright, Ateş.

1197
01:56:16,280 --> 01:56:17,280
Okay, okay.

1198
01:56:17,600 --> 01:56:18,760
This robe is enough.

1199
01:56:19,600 --> 01:56:21,000
Let’s enjoy breakfast.

1200
01:56:22,000 --> 01:56:22,960
Yes, I agree.

1201
01:56:22,961 --> 01:56:25,880
This much sentiment is too much for us.

1202
01:56:26,240 --> 01:56:27,240
Tea?

1203
01:56:27,720 --> 01:56:28,720
Please.

1204
01:56:42,840 --> 01:56:43,840
Thank you.

1205
01:56:45,520 --> 01:56:47,400
Look, I even put your favorite jam.

1206
01:56:50,040 --> 01:56:51,040
Open your mouth.

1207
01:56:53,720 --> 01:56:56,320
Very nice, I was so hungry.

1208
01:57:07,200 --> 01:57:08,440
Take your pancake too.

1209
01:57:09,400 --> 01:57:10,400
Put this over there.

1210
01:57:16,760 --> 01:57:19,880
Come on, eat, or I’ll finish it
all, nothing will be left for you.

1211
01:57:22,000 --> 01:57:23,200
You wouldn’t do that to me.

1212
01:57:24,240 --> 01:57:25,240
You think so.

1213
01:57:35,360 --> 01:57:37,360
I told you, you wouldn’t do that.

1214
01:57:40,600 --> 01:57:41,800
Come on.

1215
01:57:42,840 --> 01:57:43,840
Eat something.

1216
01:57:57,480 --> 01:57:59,680
I’m as sure as can be
that it’s the same slipper.

1217
01:58:03,000 --> 01:58:04,840
How could I forget?

1218
01:59:52,960 --> 01:59:54,160
Good morning.

1219
01:59:55,000 --> 01:59:56,000
Good morning.

1220
01:59:58,080 --> 01:59:59,080
Good morning.

1221
01:59:59,600 --> 02:00:00,600
Good morning.

1222
02:00:05,160 --> 02:00:06,160
Yaşar.

1223
02:00:08,960 --> 02:00:12,360
Zahide, what do you say? Say it
loudly, I can’t hear you, can’t you see?

1224
02:00:19,680 --> 02:00:20,680
Coffee?

1225
02:00:21,240 --> 02:00:22,560
Come get us some coffee.

1226
02:00:25,400 --> 02:00:26,919
No, I won’t get coffee.

1227
02:00:26,920 --> 02:00:28,040
Yaşar.

1228
02:00:30,200 --> 02:00:32,120
I can bring it to you later if you want.

1229
02:00:35,400 --> 02:00:36,400
Is Mercan okay?

1230
02:00:37,400 --> 02:00:38,400
They’re fine.

1231
02:00:42,880 --> 02:00:44,959
Luckily, nothing happened.
Luckily, nothing happened.

1232
02:00:44,960 --> 02:00:47,520
Otherwise, Ateş would have
torn your brother apart.

1233
02:00:48,760 --> 02:00:49,760
Yaşar!

1234
02:00:52,920 --> 02:00:56,599
What? I’m telling the
truth, isn’t it? Is it normal?

1235
02:00:56,600 --> 02:01:00,360
And why would you kidnap a married
woman? What era do you live in?

1236
02:01:00,520 --> 02:01:02,560
I think you should stay quiet now, okay?

1237
02:01:04,200 --> 02:01:05,200
Demet, my dear.

1238
02:01:07,800 --> 02:01:12,960
Don’t be upset. If she hadn’t brought up this
clumsy topic, I wouldn’t have said a word.

1239
02:01:19,680 --> 02:01:22,160
Also, what your brother did
doesn’t concern you at all.

1240
02:01:22,920 --> 02:01:25,080
I don’t think Mercan
will care about it either.

1241
02:01:26,600 --> 02:01:28,880
Wait a minute, did I say
something wrong just now?

1242
02:01:29,200 --> 02:01:33,880
Oh Yaşar, please, come on, let’s
work, come on. Come on, my dear.

1243
02:01:53,520 --> 02:01:55,240
Come on, open your phone, sister.

1244
02:01:57,320 --> 02:01:59,240
Open that phone, Demet.

1245
02:02:13,280 --> 02:02:20,560
Even though he knows I’m in trouble,
he still doesn’t open the phone.

1246
02:02:42,600 --> 02:02:43,600
You’re beautiful again.

1247
02:02:47,880 --> 02:02:49,720
But… where are you going?

1248
02:02:51,480 --> 02:02:53,719
We’re going… to the company.

1249
02:02:53,720 --> 02:02:58,080
No, I won’t stay long
anyway. You stay home and rest.

1250
02:02:58,880 --> 02:03:01,840
No, sir. I need to work.

1251
02:03:02,880 --> 02:03:05,440
I don’t want to stay home alone and think.

1252
02:03:06,760 --> 02:03:08,800
Should I stay alone here?

1253
02:03:10,280 --> 02:03:12,960
I feel safer with you. Isn’t that right?

1254
02:03:16,640 --> 02:03:18,080
You also know where I’ll hit.

1255
02:03:20,840 --> 02:03:22,000
Alright, fine.

1256
02:03:22,760 --> 02:03:26,320
And we’ve really neglected that
Italy matter. I’ll take care of it.

1257
02:03:26,680 --> 02:03:30,320
Okay. When I say we’re
going home, you won’t object.

1258
02:03:54,520 --> 02:03:55,560
Very quiet today?

1259
02:03:56,880 --> 02:04:00,559
I’m just not in the mood. You
know what happened at the mansion.

1260
02:04:00,560 --> 02:04:03,680
I got upset about them. My mother
has been a bit down for two days too.

1261
02:04:07,800 --> 02:04:08,800
You’re right.

1262
02:04:12,520 --> 02:04:14,160
Is it only about the mansion?

1263
02:04:15,320 --> 02:04:16,840
What about my mother?

1264
02:04:17,480 --> 02:04:20,080
She’s doing everything she can
to make the atmosphere more tense.

1265
02:04:32,760 --> 02:04:34,040
Breakfast isn’t ready, is it?

1266
02:04:34,320 --> 02:04:36,080
Ready. Come sit, brother.

1267
02:04:37,960 --> 02:04:39,640
Come on, let’s go.

1268
02:04:42,640 --> 02:04:45,240
Why do you look so unhappy?

1269
02:04:50,840 --> 02:04:53,960
Nothing, dear. Come, sit.

1270
02:04:55,480 --> 02:04:58,600
You sit, I’ll serve you tea.

1271
02:04:58,760 --> 02:04:59,920
Sit, my dear, come.

1272
02:05:23,840 --> 02:05:26,480
Mother, what are you doing
here? Didn’t you leave?

1273
02:05:36,400 --> 02:05:38,320
She definitely came to
make a sarcastic comment.

1274
02:05:43,280 --> 02:05:44,280
Mother, why did you come?

1275
02:05:45,920 --> 02:05:47,520
I couldn’t go, Malik.

1276
02:05:49,720 --> 02:05:51,720
I didn’t want to leave
on bad terms with you.

1277
02:05:56,000 --> 02:06:00,840
As a mother, I came to apologize.

1278
02:06:10,000 --> 02:06:15,720
Malik, son, saying “mother and father” doesn’t
mean you can just slam the door and leave.

1279
02:06:19,480 --> 02:06:21,440
You can’t leave angry like that.

1280
02:06:22,320 --> 02:06:24,480
Whatever you went
through, you went through.

1281
02:06:27,520 --> 02:06:29,320
That’s not appropriate.

1282
02:06:40,640 --> 02:06:42,560
I said I would forgive
you on one condition.

1283
02:06:46,080 --> 02:06:52,120
I came to say that I was wrong.

1284
02:07:04,000 --> 02:07:06,720
I apologize to all of you.

1285
02:07:30,800 --> 02:07:33,160
Please, let me offer you some tea.

1286
02:07:34,760 --> 02:07:38,320
No, thank you. I need to go.

1287
02:08:23,240 --> 02:08:24,240
Hello.

1288
02:08:25,960 --> 02:08:28,800
My dear sister, it’s me. Listen to me.

1289
02:08:42,200 --> 02:08:45,080
Brother, what do you think you’re doing?

1290
02:08:45,760 --> 02:08:46,800
Just listen to me.

1291
02:08:47,960 --> 02:08:52,040
What will I listen to? What do you mean,
kidnapping Mercan, how can you do such a thing?

1292
02:08:53,280 --> 02:08:54,960
And she doesn’t even love you.

1293
02:08:55,800 --> 02:08:56,800
I do love her.

1294
02:08:58,040 --> 02:08:59,040
Isn’t that enough?

1295
02:09:00,920 --> 02:09:03,200
I’ve been in love with Mercan
as long as I can remember.

1296
02:09:05,000 --> 02:09:07,680
No, no, you’re insane.

1297
02:09:09,480 --> 02:09:11,920
This isn’t love.

1298
02:09:12,560 --> 02:09:15,760
You can’t involve Mercan in
your power struggle with Ateş.

1299
02:09:16,720 --> 02:09:21,000
Even the person I call my
dear doesn’t understand me.

1300
02:09:22,480 --> 02:09:25,920
As long as she’s with Ateş,
that girl’s life isn’t safe.

1301
02:09:28,280 --> 02:09:29,920
Would I harm the woman I love?

1302
02:09:31,400 --> 02:09:34,880
You’re the one harming
her by kidnapping her.

1303
02:09:35,440 --> 02:09:36,000
Demet.

1304
02:09:36,001 --> 02:09:41,240
Brother, I saw her when
she arrived at the mansion.

1305
02:09:42,080 --> 02:09:43,440
She was in a terrible state.

1306
02:09:44,440 --> 02:09:47,120
Her arms and legs were bruised and wounded.

1307
02:09:47,200 --> 02:09:49,240
She was still trying to stand.

1308
02:09:51,120 --> 02:09:53,000
You hurt her even more.

1309
02:09:55,680 --> 02:09:58,680
Please, please, brother,
don’t do it anymore.

1310
02:09:58,880 --> 02:10:00,640
You need to surrender to the police.

1311
02:10:00,760 --> 02:10:02,280
That’s the right thing for you.

1312
02:10:03,280 --> 02:10:06,160
If Ateş finds you before the
police, it won’t end well.

1313
02:10:07,760 --> 02:10:09,960
I won’t surrender to the police or anyone.

1314
02:10:11,520 --> 02:10:12,680
Look, I’m leaving here.

1315
02:10:14,200 --> 02:10:15,560
But I need your help.

1316
02:10:16,880 --> 02:10:18,280
Come to the location I’ll send you.

1317
02:10:19,120 --> 02:10:20,480
Let’s see what we’ll do, okay?

1318
02:10:21,760 --> 02:10:22,760
Where will you escape to?

1319
02:10:24,280 --> 02:10:25,920
Don’t you think about me at all?

1320
02:10:27,040 --> 02:10:28,800
I have no one else but you.

1321
02:10:39,600 --> 02:10:41,200
Okay, my dear sister.

1322
02:10:42,360 --> 02:10:43,960
That’s why I’m calling you.

1323
02:10:44,960 --> 02:10:46,360
You come, we’ll see what to do.

1324
02:10:48,360 --> 02:10:49,360
You know what to do.

1325
02:10:50,440 --> 02:10:51,680
You’ll surrender to the police.

1326
02:10:53,840 --> 02:10:54,840
You come.

1327
02:10:56,400 --> 02:10:57,560
We’ll handle the rest.

1328
02:11:01,200 --> 02:11:02,200
Okay.

1329
02:11:03,000 --> 02:11:05,160
Okay, send the location.

1330
02:11:26,920 --> 02:11:27,920
Where is he?

1331
02:11:30,360 --> 02:11:31,360
Demet, please.

1332
02:11:32,200 --> 02:11:35,440
Cemal, whatever he did,
he is still my brother.

1333
02:11:38,280 --> 02:11:40,640
Promise me you won’t harm him.

1334
02:11:42,080 --> 02:11:43,720
Demet, your brother needs to surrender.

1335
02:12:05,800 --> 02:12:07,200
Yes, Cemal?

1336
02:12:08,240 --> 02:12:10,040
Ateş, I found Nezir’s location.

1337
02:12:10,120 --> 02:12:12,480
I’m sending it to you too,
but don’t go alone, wait for me.

1338
02:12:13,400 --> 02:12:14,400
Message me.

1339
02:12:15,080 --> 02:12:16,080
Ateş.

1340
02:12:16,480 --> 02:12:17,640
Message me, Cemal.

1341
02:12:17,800 --> 02:12:22,000
Okay… if you listen, you’ll be dead anyway.

1342
02:12:25,680 --> 02:12:28,040
I have something I need
to handle. You stay home.

1343
02:12:28,560 --> 02:12:31,280
What is it so early in the morning?
Weren’t we going to the company?

1344
02:12:32,320 --> 02:12:33,600
I won’t be late.

1345
02:12:34,520 --> 02:12:35,520
I’ll come too.

1346
02:12:36,240 --> 02:12:37,320
Mercan, no.

1347
02:12:39,440 --> 02:12:40,440
Is it about Nezir?

1348
02:12:41,160 --> 02:12:43,160
You found him, and
you’re going to him, right?

1349
02:12:43,800 --> 02:12:47,800
Mercan, don’t say a word.
You will not leave this mansion.

1350
02:12:49,360 --> 02:12:50,880
Don’t get involved in this.

1351
02:13:45,560 --> 02:13:48,040
You’ll pay heavily for
everything you’ve done so far.

1352
02:13:50,080 --> 02:13:52,200
Come on, let’s reveal our cards then.

1353
02:14:49,320 --> 02:14:50,320
Your end has come.

1354
02:14:52,400 --> 02:14:54,320
You took everything from me.

1355
02:15:00,520 --> 02:15:01,520
You ruined my life.

1356
02:15:07,800 --> 02:15:09,760
You took the woman I loved from me.

1357
02:15:12,280 --> 02:15:13,800
Mercan never loved you.

1358
02:15:18,960 --> 02:15:21,680
Thinking you could make her happy
by winning over her greedy family…

1359
02:15:21,920 --> 02:15:23,960
…you thought you could
get Mercan and be happy.

1360
02:15:25,160 --> 02:15:26,160
Shut up!

1361
02:15:26,840 --> 02:15:27,840
Shut up!

1362
02:16:13,600 --> 02:16:17,920
I should have killed you from the start.

1363
02:16:23,760 --> 02:16:28,760
If you don’t kill me here and now,
I’ll be on your neck until you die, Ateş.

1364
02:16:28,920 --> 02:16:29,920
Shut your mouth!

1365
02:16:34,160 --> 02:16:38,280
I’ll risk everything to keep Mercan
from you. I’ll hang, cut, destroy.

1366
02:16:38,680 --> 02:16:39,880
I’ll risk everything, man.

1367
02:16:44,880 --> 02:16:46,360
Don’t ever say her name again.

1368
02:16:47,920 --> 02:16:48,920
Shoot.

1369
02:16:49,440 --> 02:16:50,440
Shoot, man.

1370
02:16:50,720 --> 02:16:51,720
Shoot.

1371
02:16:53,360 --> 02:16:55,320
You won’t be able to harm anyone anymore.
